						               													<description>Up and Down is played with one or two Mystique Decks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Setup:&amp;#10;Shuffle the cards and divide them into equal high face down piles for each player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player takes the top 4 cards of his pile and places them face up in front of him.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game rules:&amp;#10;The player with the highest card (card number) starts by playing this card. If there is a tie (when playing with two decks) the player with the golden card start.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After playing a card, players always refill their hand by placing the top card of their pile face up next to their other face up cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting with the second card, only cards fitting the following criteria can be played:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The card shares the colour or the suit of the last card played&amp;#10;The card number (1-5) is higher/lower than or equal to the number of the last card played (at the beginning of the game it must be higher or equal)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player does not have a fitting card, he must pass. But if he can play a card, he must.&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;If all players successively have passed, the direction (higher/lower) is changed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the rare case that all players still have to pass again, the player with the highest card begins as if a new game would start.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;End of the game:&amp;#10;As soon as a player would be allowed to refill his hand, but has no more card in his draw pile, he wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
